## Bug Found - canAutoComplete function does not include backlog status

The `canAutoComplete` function in `packages/core/src/types/plan.ts` does NOT include the new `backlog` status in its calculation of non-closed tasks.

### Current code (line 572-586):
```typescript
export function canAutoComplete(taskStatusCounts: Record<TaskStatus, number>): boolean {
  const closedCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.CLOSED] || 0;
  const inProgressCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.IN_PROGRESS] || 0;
  const blockedCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.BLOCKED] || 0;
  const openCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.OPEN] || 0;
  const deferredCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.DEFERRED] || 0;

  // Missing: backlog count!

  const totalTasks = closedCount + inProgressCount + blockedCount + openCount + deferredCount;
  const nonClosedTasks = inProgressCount + blockedCount + openCount + deferredCount;

  return totalTasks > 0 && nonClosedTasks === 0;
}
```

### Problem:
If a plan has tasks in backlog status, those tasks are not counted. This means:
1. Backlog tasks don't contribute to `totalTasks`
2. Backlog tasks don't contribute to `nonClosedTasks`
3. A plan could incorrectly auto-complete even when backlog tasks still exist

### Fix Required:
Add `backlogCount` to the function and include it in both `totalTasks` and `nonClosedTasks` calculations:
```typescript
const backlogCount = taskStatusCounts[TaskStatus.BACKLOG] || 0;
const totalTasks = closedCount + inProgressCount + blockedCount + openCount + deferredCount + backlogCount;
const nonClosedTasks = inProgressCount + blockedCount + openCount + deferredCount + backlogCount;
```

### Also needed:
Add test case for backlog status in `packages/core/src/types/plan.test.ts` in the `canAutoComplete` describe block:
```typescript
test('returns false when tasks are in backlog', () => {
  expect(canAutoComplete(createTaskStatusCounts({
    [TaskStatus.CLOSED]: 5,
    [TaskStatus.BACKLOG]: 1,
  }))).toBe(false);
});
```

